        <item>
            <title>32: Asymcar 32: Running the Numbers</title>
            <link>http://5by5.tv/asymcar/32</link>
            <guid isPermalink="false">http://5by5.tv/asymcar/32</guid>
            <pubDate>Fri, 06 May 2016 18:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <author>Horace Dediu &amp; Jim Zellmer</author>
            <description>Anton Wahlman joins us as we dive into numbers, production curves and the clash between reality, vision and hubris over autonomous cars

                Tesla's "financial equation" merits much discussion interspersed with reflections on an EV landscape littered with government subsidies.

                We close with accounting, including a dissertation on variable costs and the burden of "dealerless" car sales.
            </description>
            <enclosure url="http://fdlyr.co/d/asymcar/cdn.5by5.tv/audio/broadcasts/asymcar/2016/asymcar-032.mp3" length="26764183" type="audio/mpeg"/>
            <content:encoded>&lt;p&gt;Anton Wahlman joins us as we dive into numbers, production curves and the clash between reality, vision and hubris over autonomous cars&lt;/p&gt;

                &lt;p&gt;Tesla's "financial equation" merits much discussion interspersed with reflections on an EV landscape littered with government subsidies.&lt;/p&gt;

